properties.description: A presence/absence tree cover dataset is derived from SPOT Panchromatic imagery (10m pixels) by a combination of digital classification and visual interpretation . The presence/absence dataset is then grouped into three density classes (Dense, Medium, Scattered) by neighbourhood and proximity cell based analysis. The raster dataset is converted to vector as a final step. Tree cover is defined as woody vegetation greater than 2 metres in height and with a crown cover (foliar density) greater than 10 percent.
